==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Huia bird
<hw>Hu"ia bird`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[Native name; -- so called from
its cry.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A New Zealand starling
(<spn>Heteralocha acutirostris</spn>), remarkable for the great
difference in the form and length of the bill in the two sexes, that of
the male being sharp and straight, that of the female much longer and
strongly curved.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Huisher</ent>⟦br⟧
